%global packname  SAFD
%global packver   2.1
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          2.1
Release:          3%{?dist}%{?buildtag}
Summary:          Statistical Analysis of Fuzzy Data

License:          GPL (>= 2)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
The aim of the package is to provide some basic functions for doing
statistics with one dimensional Fuzzy Data (in the form of polygonal fuzzy
numbers). In particular, the package contains functions for the basic
operations on the class of fuzzy numbers (sum, scalar product, mean,
median, Hukuhara difference) as well as for calculating (Bertoluzza)
distance and sample variance. Moreover a function to simulate fuzzy random
variables and bootstrap tests for the equality of means is included.
Version 2.1 fixes some bugs of previous versions.

